Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Trim the @carrots{3}(cut into 5cm long batons), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Peel the @garlic cloves{2} but leave them whole.

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.5%tsp}.

Add the potatoes and garlic cloves to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%mins}.

== Roasted Veg and Sausages ==

Meanwhile, pop the @British Cumberland sausages{8} and carrots onto a large #baking tray{} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Season the carrots with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the carrots are tender and the sausages are browned and cooked through, ~{18-20%mins}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw sausages. They're cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%grams} stems lengthways.

When about 10 mins of roasting time remain, add the Tenderstem® to another baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use another tray if necessary.

Roast on the middle shelf for the remaining time until the broccoli is tender and crispy, ~{8-10%mins}.

If you'd prefer to, boil your broccoli in step 4 while the jus cooks, until just tender, ~{3-4%mins}. Once cooked, drain and return to the pan. Drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper.

== Red Wine Gravy ==

While everything roasts, pour the @water for the jus{150%ml} into a small #saucepan{} and bring to the boil on high heat.

Stir in the @Red Wine Jus Paste{15%grams}, then reduce the heat to medium-high.

> TIP: If your red wine jus paste has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{5-6%mins}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed, then remove from the heat and cover with a #lid{} or #foil{} to keep warm.

== Garlic Mash ==

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @?milk{1%splash} (if you have any), then mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover with a lid to keep warm.

== To Serve ==

Share the garlic mash between your plates.

Top with the sausages, then pour over the red wine jus (reheat first if needed).

Serve the roasted carrots and Tenderstem® broccoli alongside. Enjoy!